Detailed Description

A wrapper for the VME library APIs.

This is the VME library wrapper, used by the application to perform VME comunications. You can change the implementation of each method (and keep the external public interface) to comply with your specific VME library APIs

bool VMEWrapper::ClearBitmaskReg ( UINT32  reg_offset,
UINT32  reg_value 
)

Clear register bitmask.

This method clears the bits setted in the reg_value parameter. The clear is perfomed by a read and write operation using the WriteReg and ReadReg wrapper methods. You can reimplement this if your VME library provides a native API.

Parameters:
reg_offset The offset (relative to the board base address) offset of the affected register
reg_value The bitmask applied
Returns:
true if the operation completed successfully

bool VMEWrapper::End ( void   ) 

End of connection.

This method is called once for closing the VME connecion: it have to get release all the resources allocated by the VME library. The connection handle must be invalidated and no more available for further comunications.

Returns:
true if VME connection closing was succesfully completed

bool VMEWrapper::Init ( const InputData &  input_data  ) 

Connection initialization.

This method is called once for each VME connection session : it have to perform all the specific initialization tasks required by your VME library, in order to get a valid connection handle.

Parameters:
input_data The input data structure passed
Returns:
true if VME connection opening was succesfully completed
